73a1bf8dc7d9"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This definition of algebraic step is more easily conveyed in terms of ",
 ButtonBox["Outer",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:ref/Outer"],
 ", but if implemented literally it would lead to an intrinsically \
inefficient algorithm, for which ",
 ButtonBox["Timing",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:ref/Timing"],
 " would scale quadratically with respect to the size of the input arguments. \
Thus, the actual algorithm implemented by ",
 Cell[BoxData["AlgebraicRange"], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
  "ce03fafc-5f19-4c6a-bc7b-5cb7c78dad0a"],
 " generates output equivalent to ",
 ButtonBox["Outer",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:ref/Outer"],
 " but is internally more refined - crucially leveraging the function ",
 ButtonBox["Nearest",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:ref/Nearest"],
 " inside ",
 ButtonBox["For",
  BaseStyle->"Link",
  ButtonData->"paclet:ref/For"],
 " loops - and effectively scales with linear time complexity."
}], "Notes",
 TaggingRules-><|
