41c8026f66dd"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The algebraic numbers thus generated can often be in a great number, with a \
tendency to accumulate towards certain points. To avoid these features, a \
further fourth argument ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[Cell[TextData[Cell[BoxData[
    FormBox["d", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
    "584574b0-2f07-4e40-b544-571b1ee7b4a7"]],ExpressionUUID->
    "632e8725-4bd6-4ad8-a134-f4448b2fe3fd"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f22a0730-6ca5-474e-bf3b-9f7a0c0723ce"],
 " can be optionally provided to require a minimum (absolute value) \
difference between successive algebraics, that is a lower bound for all the \
steps. This truncation process typically leads to a nearly uniform \
distribution of numeric values."
}], "Notes",
